b.font: Visualisation, Organisation and processing of spatial data:

div.p: To connect information to maps is not enough. We need to bring the geodata into a usable structure and in many cases (Organisation), we need to make changes to the data so they can serve our purposes (Processing). Furthermore, it is imperative to visualise the geodata in a way so we can communicate the relevant information (Visualisation).Â

b.font: Spatial Analyses to reveal connections between spatial data features:

div.p: Simply visualizing data falls short of its full potential. We can unlock deeper insights by applying various analysis techniques to gain a comprehensive understanding of situations and circumstances.
